58CachedImage::CachedImage(CachedResourceRequest&& request, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar)
59 : CachedResource(WTFMove(request), Type::ImageResource, sessionID, cookieJar)
60 , m_updateImageDataCount(0)
61 , m_isManuallyCached(false)
62 , m_shouldPaintBrokenImage(true)
63 , m_forceUpdateImageDataEnabledForTesting(false)
64{
65 setStatus(Unknown);
66}

68CachedImage::CachedImage(Image* image, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar)
69 : CachedResource(URL(), Type::ImageResource, sessionID, cookieJar)
70 , m_image(image)
71 , m_updateImageDataCount(0)
72 , m_isManuallyCached(false)
73 , m_shouldPaintBrokenImage(true)
74 , m_forceUpdateImageDataEnabledForTesting(false)
75{

78CachedImage::CachedImage(const URL& url, Image* image, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar, const String& domainForCachePartition)
79 : CachedResource(url, Type::ImageResource, sessionID, cookieJar)
80 , m_image(image)
81 , m_updateImageDataCount(0)
82 , m_isManuallyCached(true)
83 , m_shouldPaintBrokenImage(true)
84 , m_forceUpdateImageDataEnabledForTesting(false)
85{
86 m_resourceRequest.setDomainForCachePartition(domainForCachePartition);
87
88 // Use the incoming URL in the response field. This ensures that code using the response directly,
89 // such as origin checks for security, actually see something.
90 m_response.setURL(url);
91}

93CachedImage::~CachedImage()
94{
95 clearImage();
96}

98void CachedImage::load(CachedResourceLoader& loader)
99{
100 m_skippingRevalidationDocument = makeWeakPtr(loader.document());
101 if (loader.shouldPerformImageLoad(url()))
102 CachedResource::load(loader);
103 else
104 setLoading(false);
105}

107void CachedImage::setBodyDataFrom(const CachedResource& resource)
108{
109 ASSERT(resource.type() == type());
110 const CachedImage& image = static_cast<const CachedImage&>(resource);
111
112 CachedResource::setBodyDataFrom(resource);
113
114 m_image = image.m_image;
115 m_imageObserver = image.m_imageObserver;
116 if (m_imageObserver)
117 m_imageObserver->cachedImages().add(this);
118
119 if (m_image && is<SVGImage>(*m_image))
120 m_svgImageCache = makeUnique<SVGImageCache>(&downcast<SVGImage>(*m_image));
121}
122
123void CachedImage::didAddClient(CachedResourceClient& client)
124{
125 if (m_data && !m_image && !errorOccurred()) {
126 createImage();
127 m_image->setData(m_data.copyRef(), true);
128 }
129
130 ASSERT(client.resourceClientType() == CachedImageClient::expectedType());
131 if (m_image && !m_image->isNull())
132 static_cast<CachedImageClient&>(client).imageChanged(this);
133
134 if (m_image)
135 m_image->startAnimationAsynchronously();
136
137 CachedResource::didAddClient(client);
138}
139
140void CachedImage::didRemoveClient(CachedResourceClient& client)
141{
142 ASSERT(client.resourceClientType() == CachedImageClient::expectedType());
143
144 m_pendingContainerContextRequests.remove(&static_cast<CachedImageClient&>(client));
145 m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.remove(&static_cast<CachedImageClient&>(client));
146
147 if (m_svgImageCache)
148 m_svgImageCache->removeClientFromCache(&static_cast<CachedImageClient&>(client));
149
150 CachedResource::didRemoveClient(client);
151
152 static_cast<CachedImageClient&>(client).didRemoveCachedImageClient(*this);
153}
154
155bool CachedImage::isClientWaitingForAsyncDecoding(CachedImageClient& client) const
156{
157 return m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.contains(&client);
158}
159
160void CachedImage::addClientWaitingForAsyncDecoding(CachedImageClient& client)
161{
162 ASSERT(client.resourceClientType() == CachedImageClient::expectedType());
163 if (m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.contains(&client))
164 return;
165 if (!m_clients.contains(&client)) {
166 // If the <html> element does not have its own background specified, painting the root box
167 // renderer uses the style of the <body> element, see RenderView::rendererForRootBackground().
168 // In this case, the client we are asked to add is the root box renderer. Since we can't add
169 // a client to m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding unless it is one of the m_clients, we are going
170 // to cancel the repaint optimization we do in CachedImage::imageFrameAvailable() by adding
171 // all the m_clients to m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.
172 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedImageClient> walker(m_clients);
173 while (auto* client = walker.next())
174 m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.add(client);
175 } else
176 m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.add(&client);
177}
178
179void CachedImage::removeAllClientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding()
180{
181 if (m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.isEmpty() || !hasImage() || !is<BitmapImage>(image()))
182 return;
183 downcast<BitmapImage>(image())->stopAsyncDecodingQueue();
184 for (auto* client : m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding)
185 client->imageChanged(this);
186 m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.clear();
187}
188
189void CachedImage::switchClientsToRevalidatedResource()
190{
191 ASSERT(is<CachedImage>(resourceToRevalidate()));
192 // Pending container size requests need to be transferred to the revalidated resource.
193 if (!m_pendingContainerContextRequests.isEmpty()) {
194 // A copy of pending size requests is needed as they are deleted during CachedResource::switchClientsToRevalidateResouce().
195 ContainerContextRequests switchContainerContextRequests;
196 for (auto& request : m_pendingContainerContextRequests)
197 switchContainerContextRequests.set(request.key, request.value);
198 CachedResource::switchClientsToRevalidatedResource();
199 CachedImage& revalidatedCachedImage = downcast<CachedImage>(*resourceToRevalidate());
200 for (auto& request : switchContainerContextRequests)
201 revalidatedCachedImage.setContainerContextForClient(*request.key, request.value.containerSize, request.value.containerZoom, request.value.imageURL);
202 return;
203 }
204
205 CachedResource::switchClientsToRevalidatedResource();
206}
207
208void CachedImage::allClientsRemoved()
209{
210 m_pendingContainerContextRequests.clear();
211 m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.clear();
212 if (m_image && !errorOccurred())
213 m_image->resetAnimation();
214}

216std::pair<Image*, float> CachedImage::brokenImage(float deviceScaleFactor) const
217{
218 if (deviceScaleFactor >= 3) {
219 static NeverDestroyed<Image*> brokenImageVeryHiRes(&Image::loadPlatformResource("missingImage@3x").leakRef());
220 return std::make_pair(brokenImageVeryHiRes, 3);
221 }
222
223 if (deviceScaleFactor >= 2) {
224 static NeverDestroyed<Image*> brokenImageHiRes(&Image::loadPlatformResource("missingImage@2x").leakRef());
225 return std::make_pair(brokenImageHiRes, 2);
226 }
227
228 static NeverDestroyed<Image*> brokenImageLoRes(&Image::loadPlatformResource("missingImage").leakRef());
229 return std::make_pair(brokenImageLoRes, 1);
230}
231
232bool CachedImage::willPaintBrokenImage() const
233{
234 return errorOccurred() && m_shouldPaintBrokenImage;
235}
236
237Image* CachedImage::image()
238{
239 if (errorOccurred() && m_shouldPaintBrokenImage) {
240 // Returning the 1x broken image is non-ideal, but we cannot reliably access the appropriate
241 // deviceScaleFactor from here. It is critical that callers use CachedImage::brokenImage()
242 // when they need the real, deviceScaleFactor-appropriate broken image icon.
243 return brokenImage(1).first;
244 }
245
246 if (m_image)
247 return m_image.get();
248
249 return &Image::nullImage();
250}
251
252Image* CachedImage::imageForRenderer(const RenderObject* renderer)
253{
254 if (errorOccurred() && m_shouldPaintBrokenImage) {
255 // Returning the 1x broken image is non-ideal, but we cannot reliably access the appropriate
256 // deviceScaleFactor from here. It is critical that callers use CachedImage::brokenImage()
257 // when they need the real, deviceScaleFactor-appropriate broken image icon.
258 return brokenImage(1).first;
259 }
260
261 if (!m_image)
262 return &Image::nullImage();
263
264 if (m_image->isSVGImage()) {
265 Image* image = m_svgImageCache->imageForRenderer(renderer);
266 if (image != &Image::nullImage())
267 return image;
268 }
269 return m_image.get();
270}

272bool CachedImage::hasSVGImage() const

274 return m_image && m_image->isSVGImage();

277void CachedImage::setContainerContextForClient(const CachedImageClient& client, const LayoutSize& containerSize, float containerZoom, const URL& imageURL)
278{
279 if (containerSize.isEmpty())
280 return;
281 ASSERT(containerZoom);
282 if (!m_image) {
283 m_pendingContainerContextRequests.set(&client, ContainerContext { containerSize, containerZoom, imageURL });
284 return;
285 }
286
287 if (!m_image->isSVGImage()) {
288 m_image->setContainerSize(containerSize);
289 return;
290 }
291
292 m_svgImageCache->setContainerContextForClient(client, containerSize, containerZoom, imageURL);
293}
294
295FloatSize CachedImage::imageSizeForRenderer(const RenderElement* renderer, SizeType sizeType) const
296{
297 if (!m_image)
298 return { };
299
300 if (is<SVGImage>(*m_image) && sizeType == UsedSize)
301 return m_svgImageCache->imageSizeForRenderer(renderer);
302
303 return m_image->size(renderer ? renderer->imageOrientation() : ImageOrientation(ImageOrientation::FromImage));
304}
305
306
307LayoutSize CachedImage::unclampedImageSizeForRenderer(const RenderElement* renderer, float multiplier, SizeType sizeType) const
308{
309 LayoutSize imageSize = LayoutSize(imageSizeForRenderer(renderer, sizeType));
310 if (imageSize.isEmpty() || multiplier == 1.0f)
311 return imageSize;
312
313 float widthScale = m_image->hasRelativeWidth() ? 1.0f : multiplier;
314 float heightScale = m_image->hasRelativeHeight() ? 1.0f : multiplier;
315 imageSize.scale(widthScale, heightScale);
316 return imageSize;
317}
318
319LayoutSize CachedImage::imageSizeForRenderer(const RenderElement* renderer, float multiplier, SizeType sizeType) const
320{
321 auto imageSize = unclampedImageSizeForRenderer(renderer, multiplier, sizeType);
322 if (imageSize.isEmpty() || multiplier == 1.0f)
323 return imageSize;
324
325 // Don't let images that have a width/height >= 1 shrink below 1 when zoomed.
326 LayoutSize minimumSize(imageSize.width() > 0 ? 1 : 0, imageSize.height() > 0 ? 1 : 0);
327 imageSize.clampToMinimumSize(minimumSize);
328
329 ASSERT(multiplier != 1.0f || (imageSize.width().fraction() == 0.0f && imageSize.height().fraction() == 0.0f));
330 return imageSize;
331}

339void CachedImage::notifyObservers(const IntRect* changeRect)
340{
341 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedImageClient> w(m_clients);
342 while (CachedImageClient* c = w.next())
343 c->imageChanged(this, changeRect);
344}

346void CachedImage::checkShouldPaintBrokenImage()

352}

363
364void CachedImage::clear()
365{
366 destroyDecodedData();
367 clearImage();
368 m_pendingContainerContextRequests.clear();
369 m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.clear();
370 setEncodedSize(0);
371}
372
373inline void CachedImage::createImage()
374{
375 // Create the image if it doesn't yet exist.
376 if (m_image)
377 return;
378
379 m_imageObserver = CachedImageObserver::create(*this);
380
381 m_image = Image::create(*m_imageObserver);
382
383 if (m_image) {
384 if (is<SVGImage>(*m_image))
385 m_svgImageCache = makeUnique<SVGImageCache>(&downcast<SVGImage>(*m_image));
386
387 // Send queued container size requests.
388 if (m_image->usesContainerSize()) {
389 for (auto& request : m_pendingContainerContextRequests)
390 setContainerContextForClient(*request.key, request.value.containerSize, request.value.containerZoom, request.value.imageURL);
391 }
392 m_pendingContainerContextRequests.clear();
393 m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.clear();
394 }
395}

449inline void CachedImage::clearImage()
450{
451 if (!m_image)
452 return;
453
454 if (m_imageObserver) {
455 m_imageObserver->cachedImages().remove(this);
456
457 if (m_imageObserver->cachedImages().isEmpty()) {
458 ASSERT(m_imageObserver->hasOneRef());
459 m_image->setImageObserver(nullptr);
460 }
461
462 m_imageObserver = nullptr;
463 }
464
465 m_image = nullptr;
466 m_lastUpdateImageDataTime = { };
467 m_updateImageDataCount = 0;
468}
469
470void CachedImage::updateBufferInternal(SharedBuffer& data)
471{
472 m_data = &data;
473 setEncodedSize(m_data->size());
474 createImage();
475
476 // Don't update the image with the new buffer very often. Changing the decoder
477 // internal data and repainting the observers sometimes are very expensive operations.
478 if (!m_forceUpdateImageDataEnabledForTesting && shouldDeferUpdateImageData())
479 return;
480
481 EncodedDataStatus encodedDataStatus = EncodedDataStatus::Unknown;
482
483 if (isPostScriptResource()) {
484#if PLATFORM(MAC) && !USE(WEBKIT_IMAGE_DECODERS)
485 // Delay updating the image with the PostScript data till all the data
486 // is received so it can be converted to PDF data.
487 return;
488#else
489 // Set the encodedDataStatus to Error so loading this image will be canceled.
490 encodedDataStatus = EncodedDataStatus::Error;
491#endif
492 } else {
493 // Have the image update its data from its internal buffer. Decoding the image data
494 // will be delayed until info (like size or specific image frames) are queried which
495 // usually happens when the observers are repainted.
496 encodedDataStatus = updateImageData(false);
497 }
498
499 if (encodedDataStatus > EncodedDataStatus::Error && encodedDataStatus < EncodedDataStatus::SizeAvailable)
500 return;
501
502 if (encodedDataStatus == EncodedDataStatus::Error || m_image->isNull()) {
503 // Image decoding failed. Either we need more image data or the image data is malformed.
504 error(errorOccurred() ? status() : DecodeError);
505 if (m_loader && encodedDataStatus == EncodedDataStatus::Error)
506 m_loader->cancel();
507 if (inCache())
508 MemoryCache::singleton().remove(*this);
509 return;
510 }
511
512 // Tell our observers to try to draw.
513 notifyObservers();
514}
515
516bool CachedImage::shouldDeferUpdateImageData() const
517{
518 static const double updateImageDataBackoffIntervals[] = { 0, 1, 3, 6, 15 };
519 unsigned interval = m_updateImageDataCount;
520
521 // The first time through, the chunk time will be 0 and the image will get an update.
522 return (MonotonicTime::now() - m_lastUpdateImageDataTime).seconds() < updateImageDataBackoffIntervals[interval];
523}
524
525RefPtr<SharedBuffer> CachedImage::convertedDataIfNeeded(SharedBuffer* data) const
526{
527 if (!data || !isPostScriptResource())
528 return data;
529#if PLATFORM(MAC) && !USE(WEBKIT_IMAGE_DECODERS)
530 return SharedBuffer::create(PDFDocumentImage::convertPostScriptDataToPDF(data->createCFData()).get());
531#else
532 // Loading the image should have been canceled if the system does not support converting PostScript to PDF.
533 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
534 return nullptr;
535#endif
536}
537
538void CachedImage::didUpdateImageData()
539{
540 m_lastUpdateImageDataTime = MonotonicTime::now();
541 unsigned previous = m_updateImageDataCount;
542 if (previous != maxUpdateImageDataCount)
543 m_updateImageDataCount += 1;
544}
545
546EncodedDataStatus CachedImage::updateImageData(bool allDataReceived)
547{
548 if (!m_image || !m_data)
549 return EncodedDataStatus::Error;
550 EncodedDataStatus result = m_image->setData(m_data.get(), allDataReceived);
551 didUpdateImageData();
552 return result;
553}
554
555void CachedImage::updateBuffer(SharedBuffer& data)
556{
557 ASSERT(dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::BufferData);
558 updateBufferInternal(data);
559 CachedResource::updateBuffer(data);
560}
561
562void CachedImage::updateData(const uint8_t* data, unsigned length)
563{
564 ASSERT(dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::DoNotBufferData);
565 updateBufferInternal(SharedBuffer::create(data, length));
566 CachedResource::updateData(data, length);
567}
568
569void CachedImage::finishLoading(SharedBuffer* data, const NetworkLoadMetrics& metrics)
570{
571 m_data = convertedDataIfNeeded(data);
572 if (m_data) {
573 setEncodedSize(m_data->size());
574 createImage();
575 }
576
577 EncodedDataStatus encodedDataStatus = updateImageData(true);
578
579 if (encodedDataStatus == EncodedDataStatus::Error || m_image->isNull()) {
580 // Image decoding failed; the image data is malformed.
581 error(errorOccurred() ? status() : DecodeError);
582 if (inCache())
583 MemoryCache::singleton().remove(*this);
584 return;
585 }
586
587 setLoading(false);
588 notifyObservers();
589 CachedResource::finishLoading(data, metrics);
590}
591
592void CachedImage::didReplaceSharedBufferContents()
593{
594 if (m_image) {
595 // Let the Image know that the SharedBuffer has been rejigged, so it can let go of any references to the heap-allocated resource buffer.
596 // FIXME(rdar://problem/24275617): It would be better if we could somehow tell the Image's decoder to swap in the new contents without destroying anything.
597 m_image->destroyDecodedData(true);
598 }
599 CachedResource::didReplaceSharedBufferContents();
600}
601
602void CachedImage::error(CachedResource::Status status)
603{
604 checkShouldPaintBrokenImage();
605 clear();
606 CachedResource::error(status);
607 notifyObservers();
608}
609
610void CachedImage::responseReceived(const ResourceResponse& response)
611{
612 if (!m_response.isNull())
613 clear();
614 CachedResource::responseReceived(response);
615}
616
617void CachedImage::destroyDecodedData()
618{
619 bool canDeleteImage = !m_image || (m_image->hasOneRef() && m_image->isBitmapImage());
620 if (canDeleteImage && !isLoading() && !hasClients()) {
621 m_image = nullptr;
622 setDecodedSize(0);
623 } else if (m_image && !errorOccurred())
624 m_image->destroyDecodedData();
625}
626
627void CachedImage::encodedDataStatusChanged(const Image& image, EncodedDataStatus)
628{
629 if (&image != m_image)
630 return;
631
632 notifyObservers();
633}
634
635void CachedImage::decodedSizeChanged(const Image& image, long long delta)
636{
637 if (&image != m_image)
638 return;
639
640 ASSERT(delta >= 0 || decodedSize() + delta >= 0);
641 setDecodedSize(static_cast<unsigned>(decodedSize() + delta));
642}
643
644void CachedImage::didDraw(const Image& image)
645{
646 if (&image != m_image)
647 return;
648
649 MonotonicTime timeStamp = FrameView::currentPaintTimeStamp();
650 if (!timeStamp) // If didDraw is called outside of a Frame paint.
651 timeStamp = MonotonicTime::now();
652
653 CachedResource::didAccessDecodedData(timeStamp);
654}
655
656bool CachedImage::canDestroyDecodedData(const Image& image)
657{
658 if (&image != m_image)
659 return false;
660
661 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedImageClient> clientWalker(m_clients);
662 while (CachedImageClient* client = clientWalker.next()) {
663 if (!client->canDestroyDecodedData())
664 return false;
665 }
666
667 return true;
668}
669
670void CachedImage::imageFrameAvailable(const Image& image, ImageAnimatingState animatingState, const IntRect* changeRect, DecodingStatus decodingStatus)
671{
672 if (&image != m_image)
673 return;
674
675 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedImageClient> clientWalker(m_clients);
676 VisibleInViewportState visibleState = VisibleInViewportState::No;
677
678 while (CachedImageClient* client = clientWalker.next()) {
679 // All the clients of animated images have to be notified. The new frame has to be drawn in all of them.
680 if (animatingState == ImageAnimatingState::No && !m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.contains(client))
681 continue;
682 if (client->imageFrameAvailable(*this, animatingState, changeRect) == VisibleInViewportState::Yes)
683 visibleState = VisibleInViewportState::Yes;
684 }
685
686 if (visibleState == VisibleInViewportState::No && animatingState == ImageAnimatingState::Yes)
687 m_image->stopAnimation();
688
689 if (decodingStatus != DecodingStatus::Partial)
690 m_clientsWaitingForAsyncDecoding.clear();
691}
692
693void CachedImage::changedInRect(const Image& image, const IntRect* rect)
694{
695 if (&image != m_image)
696 return;
697 notifyObservers(rect);
698}
699
700void CachedImage::scheduleRenderingUpdate(const Image& image)
701{
702 if (&image != m_image)
703 return;
704
705 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedImageClient> walker(m_clients);
706 while (auto* client = walker.next())
707 client->scheduleRenderingUpdateForImage(*this);
708}
709
710bool CachedImage::currentFrameKnownToBeOpaque(const RenderElement* renderer)
711{
712 Image* image = imageForRenderer(renderer);
713 return image->currentFrameKnownToBeOpaque();
714}
715
716bool CachedImage::isOriginClean(SecurityOrigin* origin)
717{
718 ASSERT_UNUSED(origin, origin);
719 ASSERT(this->origin());
720 ASSERT(origin->toString() == this->origin()->toString());
721 return !loadFailedOrCanceled() && isCORSSameOrigin();
722}
723
724CachedResource::RevalidationDecision CachedImage::makeRevalidationDecision(CachePolicy cachePolicy) const
725{
726 if (UNLIKELY(isManuallyCached())) {
727 // Do not revalidate manually cached images. This mechanism is used as a
728 // way to efficiently share an image from the client to content and
729 // the URL for that image may not represent a resource that can be
730 // retrieved by standard means. If the manual caching SPI is used, it is
731 // incumbent on the client to only use valid resources.
732 return RevalidationDecision::No;
733 }
734 return CachedResource::makeRevalidationDecision(cachePolicy);
735}
736
737bool CachedImage::canSkipRevalidation(const CachedResourceLoader& loader, const CachedResourceRequest& request) const
738{
739 if (options().mode != request.options().mode || options().credentials != request.options().credentials || resourceRequest().allowCookies() != request.resourceRequest().allowCookies())
740 return false;
741
742 // Skip revalidation as per https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#ignore-higher-layer-caching which defines a per-document image list.
743 // This rule is loosely implemented by other browsers, we could relax it and should update it once memory cache is properly specified.
744 return m_skippingRevalidationDocument && loader.document() == m_skippingRevalidationDocument;
745}
746
747bool CachedImage::isVisibleInViewport(const Document& document) const
748{
749 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedImageClient> walker(m_clients);
750 while (auto* client = walker.next()) {
751 if (client->imageVisibleInViewport(document) == VisibleInViewportState::Yes)
752 return true;
753 }
754 return false;
755}
